<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
NEW WATER RULES TO BE MAILED TO HOMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SANTIAGO O'DONNELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Notices explaining Ventura's water conservation ordinance and outlining the 
water allocations each household will receive will be sent out today and 
Saturday, city officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The mailing to the city's 23,000 customers was first scheduled for March 23 to 
kick off the city's public information campaign concerning water conservation 
measures approved earlier this month. 
</P>
<P>
The delay was due to "glitches in the computer system that puts the mailers 
together," Ventura Public Information Officer Carol Green said. 
</P>
<P>
Under the program, which becomes effective April 12, residential users will be 
limited to 296 gallons a day, and multifamily residences to 196 gallons a day. 
Users may be given bonuses if they can document undue hardships resulting from 
the ordinance. 
</P>
<P>
The first bimonthly billing period will be a trial, with no penalties being 
assessed. But starting in mid-June, violators will be penalized with up to 10 
times the normal rate for excess use. SANTIAGO O'DONNELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
