<P>
MAN SHOT IN ARM ON HIS WAY HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Moorpark man was shot and wounded early Thursday morning as he walked to his 
home, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Ruben Navarro, 50, was listed in fair condition after being taken to St. John's 
Regional Medical Center in Oxnard, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Navarro was shot in his left arm about 2 a.m. as he walked along Los Angeles 
Avenue, Lt. Richard Diaz said. 
</P>
<P>
Diaz said detectives have not discovered a motive. 
</P>
<P>
Navarro was under heavy sedation, Diaz said. Navarro was taken to the hospital, 
more than 40 miles from the shooting, by a family member, he said. PSYCHE 
PASCUAL 
