<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PASADENA DELAYS HIRING OF NEW CITY MANAGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After two closed-door sessions, the Pasadena Board of Directors agreed Thursday 
to delay hiring a new city manager to allow more time to review each of the 
three candidates. 
</P>
<P>
Mayor William E. Thomson Jr. said members of the board, which is equivalent to 
a city council, put off the decision so they can visit the cities where each of 
the applicants is currently working. 
</P>
<P>
"The board did not make a decision and will continue deliberations to permit 
additional careful and thorough consideration to each of the three candidates," 
Thomson said. 
</P>
<P>
The board voted to meet in two weeks to make a final decision on the 
candidates: Larry Moore of Richmond, Calif.; Jack Bond of Durham, N.C., and 
Philip Hawkey of Toledo, Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
The new city manager will succeed City Manager Donald McIntire, who is retiring 
after 17 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
