<P>
MEDFLY SPRAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He doesn't fool me. State Agriculture Director Henry J. Voss hasn't scheduled a 
May malathion phase-out, instead of the original June date, out of the goodness 
of his heart. 
</P>
<P>
The primary election is in June. He (and the Republican governor who appointed 
him) doesn't want the Republican Party to be known as the pro-poison party. 
</P>
<P>
They hope people are stupid enough, in the one-month interval, to forget they 
were malathioned against their will. They also hope people don't read between 
the lines. 
</P>
<P>
Although Voss talks discontinuance, he has approved spraying some communities 
every two weeks instead of every three. Also, he doesn't promise that the state 
won't spray in the future. 
</P>
<P>
Caveat emptor. 
</P>
<P>
DORETTA ZEMP 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 
