<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
R-Rated Films Banned in Class? In what is believed to be the first such case in 
California, Martinez Superior Court Judge Richard Patsey will consider whether 
R-rated films can be banned from high school classrooms. The case involves a 
1988 suit by the San Ramon Valley Education Assn. that challenged its school 
board's policy, which keeps films ranging from "Das Boot" and "One Flew Over 
the Cuckoo's Nest" to "The Breakfast Club" from being shown to students. The 
case was originally scheduled to be taken up today but was postponed until 
April 16. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
