<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 9 GROUPS GET GRANTS FROM OLYMPIC SURPLUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Amateur Athletic Foundation of Los Angeles, the agency charged with 
disseminating Southern California's share of the 1984 Olympic surplus, 
announced nine new grants totaling $359,700. 
</P>
<P>
The largest was $150,000 to the organizing committee of the 1991 Los Angeles 
Olympic Festival for Olympic hopefuls from across the country. 
</P>
<P>
Other grants included $54,000 to the Los Angeles Throwing Center, which offers 
instructional clinics in the hammer, discus, shot put and javelin, and $13,800 
to the Mats Gymnastics Club in downtown Los Angeles. Grants also went outside 
the city to several organizations in Orange, San Diego and Imperial counties. 
</P>
