<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S TENNIS TOURNAMENT RAINED OUT AGAIN IN HOUSTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Heavy rains Thursday forced the postponement for the second day in a row of the 
$225,000 Virginia Slims of Houston women's tennis tournament. 
</P>
<P>
"We have suspended play," tournament spokesman Brian Muir said. "We did not 
complete a match for the second straight day." 
</P>
<P>
Muir said meet organizers were trying to reschedule the matches for Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The clay courts at the Westside Tennis Club proved to be too wet Wednesday 
evening when the tournament's top-seed Martina Navratilova was scheduled to 
meet Bettina Fulco of Argentina. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA033090-0103 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 197114 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 30, 1990, Friday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 2; Column 4; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
118 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
LORI MCNEIL SURPRISES SABATINI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN ANTONIO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Top-seeded Gabriela Sabatini of Argentina was ousted in the first round of the 
U.S. Women's Hardcourt Championships, losing to Lori McNeil of Houston, the 
world's 54th-ranked player, 6-3, 6-4 Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
Sabatini's loss is her first in the first round of a tournament since October 
1988, when she lost to Czechoslovakia's Jana Novatna in three sets at a 
tournament in Fielderstadt, West Germany. 
</P>
<P>
Sabatini was slapped with a code violation for illegal coaching in the last 
game of the first set. Her coach, Angel Gimenez of Spain, was sitting alone in 
the stands. 
</P>
<P>
Sabatini denied she was receiving coaching signals from Gimenez. 
</P>
<P>
"It was nothing special. Just 'Come on,' that's all," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA033090-0104 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 197121 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 30, 1990, Friday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 7; Column 3; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
35 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
