<TEXT>
<P>
Kevin Rooney, who earned millions of dollars as Mike Tyson's trainer before 
being fired in 1988, filed for bankruptcy protection after one of his homes was 
seized. 
</P>
<P>
Rooney listed more than $1.4 million in debts and no assets in his Chapter 11 
petition filed Tuesday in U.S. Bankruptcy Court in Albany, N.Y. 
</P>
</TEXT>
