</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; 
</P>
<P>
CHAMBER MAY DROP TRADITIONAL PARADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After 36 years, the once-popular Fiesta La Cristianita Parade may be canceled 
by the San Clemente Chamber of Commerce due to lack of interest. 
</P>
<P>
Although the chamber's board of directors has yet to vote on the issue, the 
parade regularly scheduled in May is not on the group's calendar this year. 
</P>
<P>
"Attendance has dwindled in the last few years," said Mimi Collier, chamber 
director. "(The parade) has been a drain on our volunteers." 
</P>
<P>
Last year, the chamber scaled down the annual event. 
</P>
<P>
Formerly a professionally run operation featuring marching bands and floats, 
the 1989 parade was a parody event run similarly to the annual Doo-Dah Parade 
in Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
The chamber also shifted the date of the parade to May from its traditional 
slot during the monthlong Fiesta La Cristianita in July. 
</P>
<P>
Collier hopes some other community group will resurrect the parade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
