<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRACK AND FIELD ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SADDLEBACK DEALS CORONA DEL MAR RARE DEFEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Corona del Mar High School boys' track and field team lost its first Sea 
View League dual meet in seven years when Saddleback beat the Sea Kings, 95-41, 
Thursday afternoon at Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar's last league loss was to Estancia in 1983. Saddleback had not 
defeated Corona del Mar in a dual track meet since 1977. 
</P>
<P>
"Actually I was a little disappointed that Corona del Mar wasn't as strong as I 
thought they would be," said Saddleback Coach Jim Knapp, whose team drenched 
him with a bucket of water upon winning the meet. "It is something, though. 
We're excited." 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback swept the discus, with Modesto Tavares winning at 142 feet 6 inches. 
In the distance events, the Roadrunners' Robby Price won the 1,600 in 4 minutes 
27 seconds, and was second in the 3,200 (10:21.7) to teammate Joe Heredia 
(10:21.5). 
</P>
<P>
In the sprints, Saddleback's Peter Colthirst won the 400 (51.7) and was second 
in the 200 (23.0); Corona del Mar's Mark Barnum won the 100 (10.9) and the 200 
(22.7). Corona del Mar's only sweep was in the pole vault, where Keith Miller 
won in a school-record 15 feet. Miller broke his record of 14-6 set two weeks 
ago. 
</P>
<P>
In other Sea View League boys' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor 70, Tustin 66 -- Brett Busch won the 110-meter hurdles (15.4) 
and 300-meter hurdles (42.4) to lead host Newport Harbor (2-2, 2-0). 
</P>
<P>
University 79, Estancia 48 -- Dan Entrikin leaped 13-0 to win the pole vault 
for host University (1-3, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
In Sea View League girls' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor 92, Tustin 35 -- Susie Jacobson won the 100 low hurdles (16.8) 
and the 300 intermediate hurdles (50.70) to lead host Newport Harbor (2-2, 
1-1). 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar 98, Saddleback 28 -- The Sea Kings (2-0) had four double winners 
